    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-04-29T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-04-29T17:00:00-05:00" n="1074"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1074">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">863.014/4–3045: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Alexander G. Kirk</persName>,
                        Political Adviser, Allied Force Headquarters, to the <gloss type="to"
                            >Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caserta</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-04-30T00:00:00+02:00"
                            >April 30, 1945—midnight</date>.<lb/>[Received April 30—10:50
                        p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1828. British Embassy Belgrade recently requested British liaison officer with
                    Fourth Yugo Army to report on Slovene claims to Austrian territory.</p>
                <p>BLO<note n="63" xml:id="d1074fn63">British Liaison Officer.</note> has replied
                    that no exact claims have been made but only following general statements:</p>
                <pb facs="1329" n="1317" xml:id="pg_1317"/>
                <p>All territory containing Slovene minority should be included in Slovenia. All
                    Stajersko and Korosko<note n="64" xml:id="d1074fn64">Styria and
                        Carinthia.</note> are rightly Slovene. Northern boundaries of these areas
                    are vague but certainly include Vijlach<note n="65" xml:id="d1074fn65"
                        >Villach.</note> and Klagenfurt and all territory south of Sava, east to
                        Dravograd<note n="66" xml:id="d1074fn66">Drauburg.</note> and possibly
                    Volkermarkt east of Dravograd; probably all territory north of Drava will be
                    claimed including Leibnitz. Tarvisio in Italy will certainly be claimed.</p>
                <p>Following Partisan troops are north of River Sava: Fourteenth Division consisting
                    of 5 brigades each about 1000 strong.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
